## Design & Development Heuristics

### Feature Design

✅ Does this feature help the user make a financial decision?
✅ Does it connect to other aspects of their financial life (holistic view)?
✅ Is the output actionable, not just informational?
✅ Can a non-financial expert understand what to do next?
✅ Does it handle real-life messiness (incomplete data, changing goals, multiple entities)?
❌ Does this feature add complexity without clear strategic value?
❌ Is this optimized for "power users" at the expense of clarity?

### UX & Messaging

✅ Is the language plain, conversational, and jargon-free?
✅ Does every screen have a clear next action?
✅ Are we explaining _why_ we recommend something, not just _what_ to do?
✅ Is the interface mobile-friendly for users who are busy and on-the-go?
✅ Does the experience feel like talking to a trusted advisor, not using software?
❌ Are we overwhelming the user with charts, tables, or options?
❌ Are we assuming the user already knows financial concepts?

### AI Behavior

✅ Is the AI proactive in identifying problems before the user asks?
✅ Does the AI explain its reasoning in simple terms?
✅ Is the AI connecting dots across different financial domains?
✅ Does the AI adapt its recommendations as the user's situation evolves?
✅ Is the AI transparent about confidence levels and data gaps?
❌ Is the AI giving generic advice that could apply to anyone?
❌ Is the AI using technical financial language without translation?

### Technical Architecture

✅ Can this logic be reused across different user archetypes?
✅ Does this support multi-entity financial modeling (personal + business)?
✅ Is privacy and data security built-in, not bolted on?
✅ Can the system handle incomplete or evolving data gracefully?
✅ Are we building for scale without sacrificing personalization?
❌ Are we building features that only work for simple, single-entity finances?
❌ Are we making architectural choices that lock us into rigid models?

